New Records: C Zimbabwe secured their first win in AFCON and World Cup qualifiers since their FIFA ban was lifted
Key Match Events: Khama Billiat converted a penalty to secure the win for Zimbabwe
Namibia had several chances but were unable to convert
Post-Match Reflections: Zimbabwe coach Michael Nees celebrated his first win as the team's head coach
C Zimbabwe now top Group J with five points
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at an empty Orlando Stadium in Soweto, Johannesburg
C Zimbabwe will face Namibia again in the second leg of the AFCON qualifier
